result.execSummary:
The defendant Dorothy M Craney was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Concurrent with: Any existing term of probation.

miscConds.notes: Costs as to Count Nos 1 and 2 are paid in full with cash bond previously posted being applied.  The remaining portion of the cash bond in the amount of $114.00 has been applied to companion citation in Waushara Co Case No. 2015TR003111.

The supervising agent will determine any necessity for the Defendant to undergo a Psychological Evaluation - soley up to the agent's discretion.  Defendant must follow any prescribed protocol by her treating mental health professionals.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
No DNA sample ordered as Defendant previously provided the same through another conviction.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.
